over i over reacted to what happened yesterday and got all giddy about it. i am going to take it one day at a freakin time and let things be. stop thinking about him and stop thinking about the possibility of us. no more. i can not figure this man out nor do i really want to. the mystery that *is* DCboy is what attracts me to him and forever will be what i am seeking. it just pisses me off that no one will *ever* meet the standard in which he has placed on my...heart? mind? body? who knows. 

i dont know that we'd be perfect for each other, let alone ideal for oen another. who the F knows. we don't really know each other that much and it kills me. i hate this roller coaster of emotions he has a way of putting me through. it kills me, but stupidly, i get off the ride and right back in line for another go. oh well. another pity party for me. woohoo

SO DC boy and i talked all day yesterday while at work on AIM. We talked mostly about sex--mainly because of a comment he/i had made the day before and we both wanted to address it further on Tuesday. it was quite the interesting day, if only a day talking about sex! and what day isn't good when all you talk about is sex...maybe a day where all you do is have sex? haah

We both have lots of hangups regarding sex/relationships and i think they might be very similar which is a good thing because we can understand one another and yet it  is a bad thing because the same things are keeping us from attempting something between the two of us. i honestly think (and i say this with all honesty and not just something optimistic) that we're both afraid of letting go and being together because we're afraid of getting hurt. Trust is an issue for both of us even if we don't voice it or identify it as a trust issue. DCboy keeps saying things like "i need to feel comfortable around someone before i'll be naked with them". Although he doesn't say that he needs to trust a girl before he'll sleep with her, it's definitely implied. and i'm in the same boat. 

I am a strong woman, independent and not afraid to be alone. BUT am also afraid to be left alone and/or hurt so i am aggressive and turn people off from me--it appears to the outside person that i don't "need you" so they say fuck off and cut me out of their life, but in reality, i am trying to just protect myself from getting hurt. And in return i attract weak men that are looking for someone to provide for them (that's not the right word, but i can't think of the word i'm looking for). All of my exes have been weak in one way or another, needing something from me and in return i gave it to them but was the dominant person in the relationship. THIS IS NOT WHAT I WANT ANY MORE. I am tried of having to be the man because these guys are too weak to grow a set. i need a guy that is just as dominant as me so that i an be submissive and be the woman. i so desire to be the woman and have someone take care of me and feel protected, but that never seems to happen. the men that are like that are usually scared off by my perceived personality and yet they never get to see the real me, the one that is actually very vulnerable and needy. i don't think that i am overly needy, just the basics. i want to be able to be myself with someone without worrying about getting hurt. 

with that said, i think that DCboy and i could be a good fit. i think he's actually dominant enough to take me, but also support me enough so that i feel comfortable with him and be myself. I also think that he has his own issues that i could support and make him feel comfortable. i think we both realize what it means and feels to be uncomfortable with someone you're with and don't want that. i think that we could be good for each other. i know that i'd never intentionally hurt and i'd never leave him for another woman, so i've got that on my side ;) and i think that if we were to try to be together he'd give it enough of a chance before wanting to find something else. it takes him a long time to build a relationship (and to subsequently sleep with someone)  that if he is going to invest that time into something he wants it to go somewhere, at least that's what i think he does, what he infact, he really does, is still a mystery to me.

so here's the dilemma... and i need HELP!!! 
if we hang out this weekend and the opportunity arises, do i sleep with him? (something i've wanted to do for almost 7 months) or hold out because the one who withholds sex has the power or tell him that i don't want it to just be about sex, it's gotta be more than that or just sleep with him and see how it goes? i fear, that with the last of those options that i am going to really like it and fall deeper into him and won't be able to get out of the hole i've dug for myself. i just don't know what to do. i've been thinking of telling him that i need more than just sex from him. that if it was only sex i wanted i could find it, but that i want something more and something more with him. 

i just don't know what to do, i'm torn. i want to sleep with him, but don't want it to just be about sex....fuck me.
hahah

so suzanne yelled at me today because i hadn't updated in a while. i guess i just haven't had anything intesting to say and had no desire to share that lack of interest with the world.

Although, i did go to boston for a long weekend with soooze and the family. it was fun. glad to get home but was fun while it lasted. warped tour was fun (but SUPER muddy!) and the freedom trail pub crawl was fun as well, i would have liked to keep crawling instead of staying Jose Macs, but still very happy to finally make it to Macs. 

i "applied" for grad school today. sorta kinda, i think. i paid the fee, so i guess i applied. i applied to Strayer University for an M Ed in Education Management. not sure if its exactly what i want (i might for the MPA instead of M Ed), but the plan is to do well in these classes so that i can show growth for when i apply to a real school. Although Strayer is over 100 years old and i thought it was just one of those crappy online schools, but i was wrong. maybe it'll be worth it. i want to get several degrees so maybe this is a good start. it's right around the corner from work so it'd be ideal to take a class or two while working here.

although not offical, i've been promoted to program officer. woohoo. i'm trying to develop my job description because the job is almost entirely open except for the duties that are MCs. I want to pick three states/urban areas to start my focus on. i'm not sure where i want to go. all the places i have any personal interest in have already been taken up by either MC or previous efforts (mainly CA and Boston/MA) so we'll see where end up. Any suggestions are welcome! i'd like to work in areas in which i know people and could ask them for advice and, mainly, see them when i'm in the area. 

ok it's after 6 and i'm still at the Fing office, i neeeeeed to go home :)

Chelsey

Ok, so it's been a stressful couple of weeks. This will be a pretty comprehensive update. i feel bad that i haven't updated in a while on here or in my 'real' journal, but i've just been too pooped to do anything and now that i've moved i'm not sure where my journal is right now....hahah 

1. the move: well the move is done. it was rough. so happy it's done. i love my new place. it's excellent. cotter (coworker) came over and helped load the truck up. at my new place some random guy and my new landlord helped unpack. thank god they came, otherwise it would have been HOURS to get things done. i was completely exhausted and mom wasn't doing so well either. so thank god they came around. Kendig was supposed to help move, but he got lost (majorly) and ended up showing up just as we were finished-literally. he followed up the last set of boxes. haha.

2. the new place: over all i love the new place. i've got mad crazy room but not a lot of closet/storage space which sucks butt, but i'm dealing. i'm not completely unpacked yet but am hoping to get things done this weekend. i spent MAD amounts of cash while moving in, hopefully i won't have to go shopping for any length of time! haha the only thing that sucks so far is the commute, it's about an hour or so. yesterday it took me 1.5 hours to get home. might have to work on that...

3. boys: 
        A. well Kevin came down and i had quite possibly the worst weekend of my life with someone, it was that bad. he was horrible. a jerk to me. made me pay for everything (except for a $2 bottle of water). and i didn't even get a thank you out of it. WTF. and secondly he's SUPER inexperience when it comes to the bedroom. it was bad. he didn't return any favors and generally seemed very disinterested in the whole idea of sex. not a normal guy by any means. i've discussed with others my thoughts on his sexuality. Is it because he's so inexperienced that he doesn't know how to treat a girl right or does he just not care b/c he's gay or something along those lines. i know it's a broad statement to claim he might be gay just based on the fact that he wasn't into me, but really, let's look at the evidence. he had a girl (a girl is a girl is a girl, no matter what she looks like) that was willing to do whatever he wanted and didn't take advantage of the situation. to top it all off HE DUMPED ME before he left. WTF i didn't know we were together and in a position to be dumped.
